                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.74/260: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-01-07T16:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 7, 1923—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 7—2:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>14. Your no. 6, January 5, 4 p.m. I am afraid that it might arouse the Japanese
                    Government to protest further to the Chinese Government were the Department at
                    this time to present a communication on the matter to the Japanese Chargé at
                    Washington. Should conditions here take a bad turn making it necessary to
                    present note to the Chinese Government I shall immediately notify the
                    Department. In that case the Department can reconsider the matter.</p>
                <p>A very optimistic view as to the chances of success with the new Cabinet is taken
                    by Mr. Barnes Moss.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
